<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>BrokenITGuy | System Logs</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600&family=Fira+Code:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.2/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        :root { --primary-teal: #00d1b2; --bg-black: #0d0d0d; --text-main: #e0e0e0; --mono-font: 'Fira Code', monospace; --body-font: 'Inter', sans-serif; --success: #39ff14; --warning: #F2A900; --fail: #ff4d4d; }
        body { background-color: var(--bg-black); background-image: url('background.png'); background-size: cover; background-position: center; background-attachment: fixed; margin: 0; display: flex; justify-content: flex-start; min-height: 100vh; color: var(--text-main); }
        .terminal-sidebar { width: 100%; max-width: 550px; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65); border-right: 1px solid rgba(0, 209, 178, 0.3); height: 100vh; overflow-y: auto; padding: 40px; box-sizing: border-box; backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
        .nav-item { font-family: var(--mono-font); text-decoration: none; color: var(--primary-teal); font-size: 1rem; display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 25px; font-weight: bold; }
        .nav-item:hover { color: #fff; text-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--primary-teal); }
        .log-entry { font-family: var(--mono-font); font-size: 0.85rem; border-left: 2px solid var(--primary-teal); padding-left: 15px; margin-bottom: 30px; line-height: 1.6; }
        .log-date { color: var(--primary-teal); font-weight: bold; }
        .status-tag { font-size: 0.7rem; padding: 2px 5px; border-radius: 2px; margin-left: 10px; font-weight: bold; }
        .SUCCESS { color: var(--success); } .WARNING { color: var(--warning); } .FAILED { color: var(--fail); } .DEGRADED { color: var(--fail); }
        .suggestion-widget { position: fixed; bottom: 20px; right: 20px; width: 260px; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85); border: 1px solid var(--primary-teal); padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; backdrop-filter: blur(10px); z-index: 1000; }
        .suggestion-widget h4 { font-family: var(--mono-font); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--primary-teal); margin: 0 0 10px 0; }
        .suggestion-widget textarea { width: 100%; background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(0, 209, 178, 0.3); color: #fff; font-family: var(--mono-font); font-size: 0.75rem; padding: 10px; box-sizing: border-box; resize: none; margin-bottom: 10px; outline: none; }
        .suggestion-widget button { width: 100%; background: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--primary-teal); color: var(--primary-teal); font-family: var(--mono-font); font-size: 0.7rem; padding: 8px; cursor: pointer; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="terminal-sidebar">
        <a href="index.html" class="nav-item">>> RETURN_TO_HOME [CLICK_HERE]</a>

        <div class="log-content">
            <div class="log-entry">
                <span class="log-date">[2026-01-28]</span> <span class="status-tag SUCCESS">LIVE</span><br>
                > SYSTEM_REBOOT successfully deployed to Netlify production.<br>
                > Standardized navigation paths to avoid local server encoding errors.<br>
                > Current Status: My spine feels like a SATA cable that's been bent too many times, but the code is clean.
            </div>

            <div class="log-entry">
                <span class="log-date">[2026-01-01]</span> <span class="status-tag SUCCESS">SUCCESS</span><br>
                > MANDATORY SOCIAL COMPLIANCE: Fixed the critical Facebook share button.<br>
                > If users can't link content to Zuckerberg's wasteland, the site is apparently useless.<br>
                > <span style="color:var(--primary-teal)">social_link_handler.js</span> stabilized.
            </div>

            <div class="log-entry">
                <span class="log-date">[2026-01-01]</span> <span class="status-tag SUCCESS">SUCCESS</span><br>
                > [CMD] FIREWALL RECONSTRUCTION COMPLETE.<br>
                > My initial UDM config was a disaster zone. Rebuilt the core ruleset from scratch.<br>
                > Sanity restored to the <span style="color:var(--primary-teal)">firewalls</span>.
            </div>

            <div class="log-entry">
                <span class="log-date">[2026-01-01]</span> <span class="status-tag DEGRADED">WARNING</span><br>
                > Physical Resources Exhausted: Human interface device reporting severe <span style="color:var(--fail)">PAIN_STATE</span>.<br>
                > Sitting duration has exceeded acceptable thresholds. Full-body resource depletion detected.<br>
                > Initiating mandatory, though delayed, system shutdown.
            </div>

            <div class="log-entry">
                <span class="log-date">[2026-01-01]</span> <span class="status-tag SUCCESS">SUCCESS</span><br>
                > [BUG] VPN TUNNEL STABILIZATION: Fixed sloppy handshakes for virtual machines on <span style="color:var(--primary-teal)">Proxmox</span>.<br>
                > Patching the VPN tunnels was supposed to be easy. It wasn't.
            </div>

            <div class="log-entry">
                <span class="log-date">[2026-01-01]</span> <span class="status-tag FAILED">ERROR</span><br>
                > [ERR] MEDIA_SERVER AUTH FAIL LOOP: Media server is acting like it doesn't know me.<br>
                > Blaming cosmic rays for the authentication hell. I hate user permissions.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="suggestion-widget">
        <form name="suggestions" method="POST" data-netlify="true">
            <h4>[ SUGGESTIONS_FEED ]</h4>
            <textarea name="message" rows="4" placeholder="Input suggestion..." required></textarea>
            <button type="submit">SEND_PACKET</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>